want to give you a

00:00:20.980 --> 00:00:21.780
broad intuition.

00:00:21.780 --> 00:00:24.950
Because in calculus class,
people-- there are all these

00:00:24.950 --> 00:00:28.120
rules, when, you know, the
second derivative is positive,

00:00:28.120 --> 00:00:29.330
you're concave this way.

00:00:29.330 --> 00:00:30.830
When the second derivative
is negative, you're

00:00:30.830 --> 00:00:31.930
concave this way.

00:00:31.930 --> 00:00:34.740
And people memorize the rules,
and they take the tests, and if

00:00:34.740 --> 00:00:36.820
